    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Let \(A = {@matrixa@}\) and \(B = {@matrixb@}.\) Compute the following matrices:</p>
<br>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
  <li><div>\((AB)^{T} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</div><div><br></div></li>
<li><div>\(B^{T}A^{T} = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</div></li>
</ol>
<p>What do you notice about the results?</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We are given the matrices \(A = {@AA@}\) and \(B = {@BB@}\) and are asked to compute the following:</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<li>
\[\begin{aligned}
(AB)^T &amp;= \left({@AB@}\right)^T \\
&amp;= \left({@ABs@}\right)^T \\
&amp;= {@ta1@}
\end{aligned}\]
</li>
<li>
\[\begin{aligned}
B^TA^T &amp;= {@BB@}^T {@AA@}^T \\
&amp;= {@BBT@} {@AAT@} \\
&amp;= {@BTAT@} \\
&amp;= {@BTATs@}
\end{aligned}\]
</li>
</ol>
<p>Note that we got the same answer for \((AB)^T\) and \(B^TA^T\). In fact, this is true in general.</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
